                            <comment id="13255071" author="kenfinni" created="Tue, 21 Jun 2016 07:46:49 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;jaxrs-client jar is provided with the modules, it may just need to be added as a maven dep on /api to make it usable&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13255495" author="heiko.braun" created="Wed, 22 Jun 2016 03:31:28 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;A quick note to myself: Many of the problems we face with using the JAXRS client API&apos;s (i.e. &quot;Could not find constructor for class: org.jboss.resteasy.core.AsynchronousDispatcher&quot; or &quot;ClassNotFoundException: org.glassfish.jersey.client.JerseyClientBuilder&quot;) derive from the fact that internally both the JAXRS client and resteasy use the default JDK service loader to discover the vendor implementation. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;By default the ServiceLoader uses the thread context classloader for loading META-INF/services. The Swarm RuntimeServer however mucks with that and replaces it with the module loader after Container#start(). In some cases (i.e. IDE main(), surefire InVM, etc) this results in weird classloading sceanrios where one half (i.e the JAXRS client API) is retrieved from the system classpath, but the other half (i.e. service provider implementations) are looked for on the module classpath, which fails. &lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
